    "recap_headline": "College of Charleston",
    "recap_text": "MT PLEASANT, S.C. \u2013\nCollege of Charleston baseball walked-off Stony Brook, 5-4, in ten innings Saturday afternoon at Patriots Point to even the series.\nCofC collected its third walk-off win of the year, improving to 8-10 and 3-2 in league while the Seawolves drop to 3-13 and 2-3 in the CAA.\nCRITICAL POINTS AGAINST STONY BROOK:\nTrailing 2-0 in the fifth, Charleston used a three-spot in the home half of the frame to take the lead.\nGraduate\nReece Holbrook\nleveled the game at two, singling in redshirt junior\nBraeden Smith\nbefore motoring around the bases in the next at bat on a freshman\nJake Amman\ndouble.\nSmith later gave the Cougars the lead again in the eighth, hitting an infield dribbler.\nIn the ninth, Stony Brook once again tied the game to send the contest to extras.\nFreshman\nNick Diaz\nled off the bottom of the tenth with a double, sending redshirt freshman\nWill Burgess\nto the plate.\nBurgess bunted to the pitcher, who airmailed the throw into the outfield, allowing Diaz to score and Charleston to even the series.\nOF NOTE:\nCharleston is now 9-2 against Stony Brook in the all-time series.\nStancil recorded a career-best 5 strikeouts Saturday.\nLyon tied Nathan Ocker (2016-19) for the second-most relief appearances in program history Saturday, pitching in his 85th career ballgame out of the bullpen.\nFive different Cougars collected multi-hit games in the win, with Amman going 3-for-5 Saturday.\nCharleston tallied a season-high 14 hits and five doubles.\nUP NEXT:\nCharleston and Stony Brook square off in the rubber match Sunday with a 1 p.m. matchup from Patriots Point.\nFor complete coverage of Charleston baseball, follow us X (@CofCBaseball) and Instagram (@CofC_Baseball)."
  },
